This is a common issue when linking C libraries in a C++ project with static runtime. The problem is that some standard C library functions are being referenced but not found. Here are several solutions:

## Solution 1: Add Missing CRT Libraries

Try adding these libraries to your linker command (in this order):

```
/LIBPATH:C:\libxml2vc\lib 
libxml2s.lib 
/LIBPATH:C:\buildzlib 
zlibstaticd.lib 
/LIBPATH:C:\GnuWin32\lib 
libiconv.lib 
bcrypt.lib 
libcmt.lib  // Add this
libcpmt.lib // Add this
oldnames.lib // Add this
/MANIFEST 
```

## Solution 2: Use Correct Linker Order

The order of libraries matters. Try this order:

```
/LIBPATH:C:\libxml2vc\lib 
/LIBPATH:C:\buildzlib 
/LIBPATH:C:\GnuWin32\lib 
/NODEFAULTLIB:MSVCRT 
/NODEFAULTLIB:MSVCRTD 
libcmt.lib 
libcpmt.lib 
oldnames.lib 
bcrypt.lib 
libxml2s.lib 
zlibstaticd.lib 
libiconv.lib 
/MANIFEST 
```

## Solution 3: Build with Consistent Runtime

Make sure all libraries (libxml2, zlib, iconv) are built with the same runtime (/MT vs /MD). If you're using /MT, all dependencies should also be built with /MT.

## Solution 4: Use MSVC Runtime Wrapper

If the above doesn't work, create a small wrapper to force the correct runtime linking:

```c
// force_crt.c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <string.h>

// Force linkage of required CRT functions
void force_crt_linkage() {
    char buffer[100];
    snprintf(buffer, sizeof(buffer), "test");
    vsnprintf(buffer, sizeof(buffer), "test", NULL);
    sscanf("test", "%s", buffer);
    floor(1.0);
    ceil(1.0);
    // Add other missing functions as needed
}
```

Compile this with your project.

## Solution 5: Check Library Compatibility

The libraries might be built with a different Visual Studio version. Make sure:
- All libraries are built with VS2008 (based on your linker version 9.00.30729.01)
- All use the same runtime (/MT for static, /MD for dynamic)

Try this minimal working command first:
```
/LIBPATH:C:\libxml2vc\lib 
/LIBPATH:C:\buildzlib 
/LIBPATH:C:\GnuWin32\lib 
libcmt.lib 
oldnames.lib 
libxml2s.lib 
zlibstaticd.lib 
libiconv.lib 
bcrypt.lib 
/MANIFEST 
```

The key is ensuring consistent runtime library usage across all dependencies.

